title: Chicago mom charged with starving baby to death - Chicago Tribune
text: Chicago mom charged with starving baby to death Shawnquail Minnis, 22 Cook County sheriff's photo / Shawnquail Minnis, 22, is charged with murder in the Nov. 5, 2014, death of her son, Jashawn McBride, who the Cook County medical examiner's office determined died at 54 days old of starvation in a homicide by neglect.
